:39Z", "updated_at": "2018-11-19T17:51:57Z", "closed_at": "2018-11-19T17:51:57Z", "author_association": "NONE", "body_html": "<p>Nop operations on empty tensors are sometimes convenient to save boiler-plate code on corner cases. PyTorch accepts many operations on empty tensors without a problem:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre>a <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> torch.Tensor()\nb <span class=\"pl-k\">=</span> (a <span class=\"pl-k\">-</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">1</span>) <span class=\"pl-k\">*</span> <span class=\"pl-c1\">5</span></pre></div>\n<p>but fails for <code>scatter_</code>:</p>\n<div class=\"highlight highlight-source-python\"><pre>torch.zeros(<span class=\"pl-c1\">10</span>).scatter_(<span class=\"pl-c1\">0</span>, torch.LongTensor(), <span class=\"pl-c1\">0.0</span>)</pre></div>", "body_text": "Nop operations on empty tensors are sometimes convenient to save boiler-plate code on corner cases. PyTorch accepts many operations on empty tensors without a problem:\na = torch.Tensor()\nb = (a - 1) * 5\nbut fails for scatter_:\ntorch.zeros(10).scatter_(0, torch.LongTensor(), 0.0)", "body": "Nop operations on empty tensors are sometimes convenient to save boiler-plate code on corner cases. PyTorch accepts many operations on empty tensors without a problem:\r\n```python\r\na = torch.Tensor()\r\nb = (a - 1) * 5\r\n```\r\n\r\nbut fails for `scatter_`:\r\n```python\r\ntorch.zeros(10).scatter_(0, torch.LongTensor(), 0.0)\r\n```"}